Source: passwordpolicy
Section: database
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Ruohang Feng <rh@vonng.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13), postgresql-all (>= 217~), libcrack2-dev (>= 2.9)
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Rules-Requires-Root: no
Homepage: https://github.com/fmbiete/passwordpolicy

Package: postgresql-PGVERSION-passwordpolicy
Architecture: any
Provides: postgresql-passwordpolicy
Depends: cracklib-runtime, ${postgresql:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: PostgreSQL password complexity policy extension
 passwordpolicy checks PostgreSQL role passwords when they are set through
 CREATE ROLE or ALTER ROLE. It must be loaded through shared_preload_libraries
 and supports dynamically configurable complexity, history, and account
 soft-lock policies.
